ng
> standing=C2=A0 misnomer convention..ha ha ha ha)
>=20
> Can you move that to scripts dir(as the subject line says) ..at least i=
t
> would be more visible to the people than hunting down some important
> tool for debugging.

Well, if you look at scripts/Makefile you'll find this in the header:

# scripts contains sources for various helper programs used throughout

# the kernel for the build process.


After reading this I decided it was the wrong place and found one that
seemed like a better fit. Sure get_maintainer.pl is in scripts/ as well,
but that's something meant to be used by developers. kernel-chktaint
OTOH is meant for users, just like most of the stuff in tools/ is, and
that's why I think it's a better fit.

Anyway: I have no strong option on this, feel free to submit a patch
that moves it. I likely will mention my reasoning for the current place
(just like I did above) but won't oppose so a move strongly.

Ciao, Thorsten


